                            <comment id="13449345" author="hossman" created="Thu, 6 Sep 2012 01:31:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;discovered a slightly larger problem dealing with dynamic copyFiels that i spun off into &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3798&quot; title=&quot;copyField logic in LukeRequestHandler is primitive, doesn&amp;#39;t work well with dynamicFields&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3798&quot;&gt;SOLR-3798&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13449347" author="hossman" created="Thu, 6 Sep 2012 01:39:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch that fixes LukeRequestHandler to return just the names for copyDests and copySources and includes a test case (part of which is commented out because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3798&quot; title=&quot;copyField logic in LukeRequestHandler is primitive, doesn&amp;#39;t work well with dynamicFields&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3798&quot;&gt;SOLR-3798&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;amazingly: this change doesn&apos;t totally break the admin ui, which leads me to believe steffkes is even more awesome then i realized, and must have made it assume the strings re field names it if can&apos;t &quot;parse&quot; them using the bogus absurd &quot;toString&quot; format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I consider this a bug fix, and would definitley like to commit unless stefkes says that it does in fact break the UI in some way i&apos;m not yet realizing.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
